⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Trial of Dmitri
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦The Trial of Dmitri:BKZ:ec60cf⟧

WHO   — The Trial of Dmitri — the miscarriage of justice
WHAT  — The world's judgement against the truth: lawyers' rhetoric, Katerina's letter, and circumstance convict the innocent ‘heart’ while the real killer is already dead.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel sets human justice — clever, eloquent, and wrong — against the deeper guilt and innocence only the reader has seen.
HOW   — By prosecution and defence, by psychology paraded as proof, and by a verdict that punishes the wish for the deed.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I convicted the right soul of the wrong crime — Dmitri was innocent of the blood and guilty of the wish, and human justice could not tell the difference.

